# Workflow and QA Rules

## Build & Deploy
- Validate build before deploy: `cd frontend && npm run build`.
- Deploy from repository ROOT (not `frontend/`).
- Pre-deploy: diff `frontend/dist/assets/index-*.js` bundle hash vs production. Stale bundle is the #1 cause of "works locally but not in prod" incidents.
- Rollback path: Firebase Hosting release history (`firebase hosting:clone`).

## QA Checklist (before marking task done)
- Region + sector switching tested across all 4 regions × 3 sectors.
- Async UI has both loading and error states — no silent failures.
- Responsive verified at 375, 768, 1024, and 1440 widths for UI-heavy changes.
- Heavy animation respects `prefers-reduced-motion`.
- Color contrast meets WCAG AA (4.5:1 for text).
- No `console.log` left in frontend code (functions logging is allowed).
- No broken `href="#"` links.
- Adjacent pages that share components still work.

## Incident Protocol
F12 Console → capture full error stack → identify whether issue is frontend (bundle hash mismatch) or function (Cloud Functions logs) → rebuild + redeploy hosting BEFORE deep-diving into code.

## Large File Safety
When editing files >500 lines, verify integrity immediately after edit.
- PowerShell line count: `(Get-Content "path").Length`
- PowerShell tail: `Get-Content "path" -Tail 40`
- Bash equivalents: `wc -l <file>` and `tail -n 40 <file>`
- Confirm `npm run build` passes before considering the edit complete.